rComments: He's very knowledgeable and always really helpful for students. The best prof I have seen in the ou engineering faculty.

Professor Javad's Power Systems class was the a pleasure to be in. He is very supportive to students and understands that we too are human and have our ups and downs sometimes. If you get to have Javad for any class, he will not let you down.
Classes are unclear and he goes through the material very fast.

Really understanding and nice, but also productive: one of the few courses I've had where we covered the entire textbook. The exams are straightforward and cover everything giving you a good representation of your progress rather than a random sample. would highly recommend.
Prof Fattahi is really a nice one and he knows this field very well. He is very kind no matter at class or after.
He's a great teacher. He explained the course with examples which is made the course be more understandable and easy. Also, he has a good cooperation with the students and answer their question.

Very condescending to students when they do not understand, therefore very unmotivational.  Unclear in lectures, all teaching was done using PowerPoints which were useless as all examples given were incomplete or had skipped steps.  I would not recommend him.
